I try to load an xgs XAudio2 engine file with following code but fail without any idea why i do get the error message FileNotFound. The file exists at specified path. I use the current developer build 3.5.0.1148 of Monogame in a Universal Windows project. My VS 2015 Community Edition is up to date with Update1 installed.

``` csharp
const string delimiter = @"\";
const string contentFolder = @"Content"; // This is normaly taken from general content path var
const string audioFolder = @"Audio" + delimiter + @"XACT" + delimiter;

// E:\Documents\Visual Studio 2015\Projects\MyProject\MyProject\bin\WindowsUAP\x86\Debug\
var root = Package.Current.InstalledLocation.Path.Replace(@"AppX", "");
// E:\Documents\Visual Studio 2015\Projects\MyProject\MyProject\bin\WindowsUAP\x86\Debug\Content\Audio\XACT\
var path = root + contentFolder + delimiter + audioFolder;
// E:\Documents\Visual Studio 2015\Projects\MyProject\MyProject\bin\WindowsUAP\x86\Debug\Content\Audio\XACT\Audiomaster.xgs
var file = path + @"Audiomaster.xgs";
// Following line crash with error see below
engine = new AudioEngine(file);
```

